As an engineer, I want to deploy the Google Cloud Storage (GCS) MCP Server to Cloud Run using Terraform and automated CI/CD pipelines, so that the AI Agent can reliably and securely interact with the GCS MCP Server in a deployed Cloud environment without managing token-based authentication at the Cloud Run instance level.

Acceptance Criteria
The GCS MCP Server deployment is instantiated via Terraform.
Authentication at the Cloud Run instance level could not be managed (yet), i.e., it could be an unauth instance.
There is a structured Terraform module specifically for this deployment, located at terraform/gcs_mcp_server_resources/.
The Terraform configuration and resource definition (terraform/gcs_mcp_server_resources/) must be fundamentally similar to the existing terraform/mcp_server_resources/ (which deploys the BigQuery MCP server).
Automated CI/CD pipelines (Cloud Build triggers) are created and configured to build and deploy the GCS MCP Server automatically when changes occur.
Integration/Unit tests for the GCS MCP Server must exist and pass successfully before deployment. These tests must be located under mcp_servers/gcs/tests/.
A valid Dockerfile must exist under mcp_servers/gcs/ to containerize the GCS MCP Server, serving as the basis for the deployment image.
The deployed GCS MCP Server must be fully accessible and testable by the Agent created in agent/core_agent.
Definition of Done
Create a new directory terraform/gcs_mcp_server_resources/ alongside the existing mcp_server_resources/.
Implement main.tf, variables.tf, and outputs.tf inside the new Terraform folder to provision:
The Google Artifact Registry repository (with the same artifact registry name: mcp-servers).
The Google Cloud Run service for the GCS MCP Server, explicitly configuring roles/run.invoker to allUsers (or the equivalent configuration to explicitly disable IDToken requirement).
The Google Cloud Build triggers mapping to the repository branches.
Verify that the new CI/CD pipelines successfully build the image using mcp_servers/gcs/Dockerfile and deploy it to the new Cloud Run instance.
Ensure automated tests are correctly placed mcp_servers/gcs/tests/ and are executed successfully locally (e.g., make run-gcs-tests) and in the CI pipeline.
Verify the deployed Cloud Run URL successfully exposes the MCP Server (e.g., via the configured StreamableHTTP endpoints) and that the remote Agent can connect to it.
Check how the BigQuery MCP Server Deployment is implemented for architectural guidance.